projekt z IPI PAN:

  • Przetworzyc Marple do postaci tekstowego pliku z atrybutami fragment/ow i werdyktem eksperta.

Atrybuty:

    • Szerokosc prazka centralnego
    • Jego jasnosc (rozumiana jako max. (po szerokosci) wzglednej jasnosci)
    • Jego asymetria i/lub skosnosc(curtosis) (sprawdzic definicje, to jest jakas kombinacja momentow)
    • Jego prostokatnosc (zdefiniowana odch.stand (sigm/a) jasnosci wzgl.)
    • Odleglosc od prazka centr. do najblizszego po prawej i po lewej.
    • Moze jakies fourierki albo transf.cosinusowa?

Dla kazdej pary fragmentow maja byc te atrybuty dla kazdego "partnera", plus werdykt eksperta; to ma byc na koniec lipca.

  • Projekt, zeby mial szanse przejscia, musi obejmowac conajmniej 3 kraje i 5-6 firm (nie wiem, czy az tyle komercyjnych, czy liczac lacznie firmy komercyjne i placowki badawcze).

  • >AOnouveaIIS conference in Bystra. They seem quite eager to try and process the MARPLE set of examples. We agreed on certain attributes which can be used to describe single striae, and, once we have distilled those attributes from the raw database files (estimated time: end of July), the Warsawers will run them through their machine inference mills. They also have established links with a high-tech company in Germany, who may become an industrial partner in the new project. I am sorry to say that the computer department of the Bydgoszcz police command were rather a disappointment in that role; while we provided them with algorithms and structures, they never got down to implementing them as fully usable systems. I can hardly blame them, given that their staff was decimated during Poland's recent reform of territorial administration, which nearly stripped Bydgoszcz of its status as regional capital. Still, I have to look for a more stable and truly _industrial_ partner in the future, and the German company may be a viable option. For our project to succeed under the 5th Framework Programme, we will need the involvement of at least 5 or six entities (institutions, institutes, and companies) from at least 3 countries. The Netherlands, Poland and Germany make 3 countries; your lab, our institute, ICS PAS and their German friends... that's 4 entities; we need a few more partners. I am thinking about the French universities of Lille and Valenciennes, the Regional Police Command in Katowice, Poland (a place much bigger and more stable in its status than Bydgoszcz), and the Dutch company who commercialized your Rebezo. I do remember about the software we promised to send you; a beta version should be ready in about a week's time now.

  • >AOnouveaIIS conference in Bystra. They seem quite eager to try and process the MARPLE set of examples. We agreed on certain attributes which can be used to describe single striae, and, once we have distilled those attributes from the raw database files (estimated time: end of July), the Warsawers will run them through their machine inference mills. They also have established links with a high-tech company in Germany, who may become an industrial partner in the new project. I am sorry to say that the computer department of the Bydgoszcz police command were rather a disappointment in that role; while we provided them with algorithms and structures, they never got down to implementing them as fully usable systems. I can hardly blame them, given that their staff was decimated during Poland's recent reform of territorial administration, which nearly stripped Bydgoszcz of its status as regional capital. Still, I have to look for a more stable and truly _industrial_ partner in the future, and the German company may be a viable option. For our project to succeed under the 5th Framework Programme, we will need the involvement of at least 5 or six entities (institutions, institutes, and companies) from at least 3 countries. The Netherlands, Poland and Germany make 3 countries; your lab, our institute, ICS PAS and their German friends... that's 4 entities; we need a few more partners. I am thinking about the French universities of Lille and Valenciennes, the Regional Police Command in Katowice, Poland (a place much bigger and more stable in its status than Bydgoszcz), and the Dutch company who commercialized your Rebezo. I do remember about the software we promised to send you; a beta version should be ready in about a week's time now.
